2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute cancer from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • some hedibX == 5 into 1
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute cancer_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if cancer == 1, cancer_age = heagg
  • if cancer == 0, cancer_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise, cancer_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1$id)
ELSA_ds_w1$cancer <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$cancer[which(ELSA_w1$hedib01 == 5 | ELSA_w1$hedib02 == 5 | ELSA_w1$hedib03 == 
    5 | ELSA_w1$hedib04 == 5 | ELSA_w1$hedib05 == 5 | ELSA_w1$hedib06 == 5 | 
    ELSA_w1$hedib07 == 5 | ELSA_w1$hedib08 == 5 | ELSA_w1$hedib09 == 5 | ELSA_w1$hedib10 == 
    5)] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w1$cancer[which(ELSA_w1$hedib01 == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w1$cancer[which(ELSA_w1$hedib01 == -8)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1$cancer_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w1$cancer == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w1$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w1$cancer == 1)] <- car::recode(ELSA_w1$heagg[which(ELSA_ds_w1$cancer == 
    1)], "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997")

2.1.2.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute cancer from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • some hedibX == 5 into 1
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute cancer_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if cancer == 1, cancer_age = HeAggRY-ybirth
  • if cancer == 0, cancer_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise, cancer_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w2$id)
ELSA_ds_w2$cancer <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$cancer[which(ELSA_w2$hedib01 == 5 | ELSA_w2$hedib02 == 5 | ELSA_w2$hedib03 == 
    5 | ELSA_w2$hedib04 == 5)] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w2$cancer[which(ELSA_w2$hedib01 == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w2$cancer[which(ELSA_w2$hedib01 == -8)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2$cancer_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$cancer == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w2$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAggRY %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9))] <- ELSA_w2$HeAggRY[which(ELSA_ds_w2$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAggRY %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9))] - ELSA_w2$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w2$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w2$HeAggRY %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9))]
ELSA_ds_w2$cancer_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w2$cancer_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;NA=999")

2.1.3.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute cancer from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • dhedibca == 1 into 1
  • dhedibca == 0 into 0
  • dhedibca == -1 into 996

To compute cancer_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if cancer == 1, cancer_age = heaggry-ybirth
  • if cancer == 0, cancer_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise, cancer_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w3 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w3$id)
ELSA_ds_w3$cancer <- car::recode(ELSA_w3$dhedibca, "-1=996")

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w3$cancer_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w3$id))
ELSA_ds_w3$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$cancer == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w3$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w3$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w3$heaggry %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)] <- ELSA_w3$heaggry[which(ELSA_ds_w3$cancer == 
    1 & !ELSA_w3$heaggry %in% c(-1, -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)] - ELSA_w3$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w3$cancer == 
    1 & !ELSA_w3$heaggry %in% c(-1, -8, -9) & ELSA_w3$ybirth != 998)]
ELSA_ds_w3$cancer_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w3$cancer_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;NA=999")

2.1.4.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute cancer from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • hedibca == 1 into 1
  • hedibca == 0 into 0
  • hedibca == -1 into 996
  • hedibca == -9 into 997
  • hedibca == -8 into 998

To compute cancer_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if cancer == 1, cancer_age = heaggry-ybirth
  • if cancer == 0, cancer_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -2 into 991
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, cancer_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w4$id)
ELSA_ds_w4$cancer <- car::recode(ELSA_w4$hedibca, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997")


# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4$cancer_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w4$id))
ELSA_ds_w4$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$cancer == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w4$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heaggry %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9, -2))] <- ELSA_w4$heaggry[which(ELSA_ds_w4$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heaggry %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9, -2))] - ELSA_w4$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w4$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w4$heaggry %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9, -2))]
ELSA_ds_w4$cancer_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w4$cancer_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;-2=991;NA=999")

2.1.5.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute cancer from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • hedibca == 1 into 1
  • hedibca == 0 into 0
  • hedibca == -1 into 996
  • hedibca == -9 into 997
  • hedibca == -8 into 998

To compute cancer_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if cancer == 1, cancer_age = heaggry-ybirth
  • if cancer == 0, cancer_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, cancer_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w5 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w5$id)
ELSA_ds_w5$cancer <- car::recode(ELSA_w5$hedibca, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997")

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w5$cancer_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w5$id))
ELSA_ds_w5$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w5$cancer == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w5$cancer_age[which(ELSA_ds_w5$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w5$heaggry %in% c(-1, 
    -8, -9))] <- ELSA_w5$heaggry[which(ELSA_ds_w5$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w5$heaggry %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9))] - ELSA_w5$ybirth[which(ELSA_ds_w5$cancer == 1 & !ELSA_w5$heaggry %in% 
    c(-1, -8, -9))]
ELSA_ds_w5$cancer_age <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w5$cancer_age, "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997;NA=999")
